1
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:58,120
Excuse me, coming through.

2
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,439
Make way, please.

3
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,040
Watch your back.

4
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,560
Watch out for the oil.

5
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,159
Watch out for the oil.

6
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,319
You're just parroting.

7
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,400
You're a salad, what oil is there?

8
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:09,400
Salad oil.

9
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,159
Tsk.

10
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:11,560
Just like that.

11
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:13,400
What are you chatting about?

12
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:15,840
Chatting about Auntie Cai's son and daughter-in-law.

13
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,759
And the grandson too.

14
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,639
Uncle Liang, why are you leaving?

15
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,879
He hates hearing about my son's mess.

16
00:02:22,199 --> 00:02:23,919
If it's as bad as you say,

17
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,960
why doesn't your son ask for a divorce?

18
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:26,879
Divorce?

19
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,919
What kind of person gets a divorce?

20
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:29,919
A coward.

21
00:02:30,039 --> 00:02:31,159
As you young people say...

22
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:31,800
What?

23
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,759
A loser.

24
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:33,479
I...

25
00:02:33,479 --> 00:02:34,520
I wasn't talking about you.

26
00:02:35,039 --> 00:02:36,599
Then you must be talking about me.

27
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:37,479
Anyway,

28
00:02:37,759 --> 00:02:38,879
a real man

29
00:02:38,879 --> 00:02:40,280
shouldn't just give up.

30
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,240
Shouldn't run away.

31
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,379
Should stand tall.

32
00:02:42,379 --> 00:02:42,860
Yes.

33
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,159
You mean...

34
00:02:44,159 --> 00:02:45,479
I don't stand tall?

35
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,039
No.

36
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:47,180
She means

37
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:49,560
you're not a real man.

38
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,060
Did I ask you to translate?

39
00:02:51,719 --> 00:02:53,379
When did I say that?

40
00:02:53,379 --> 00:02:54,800
When did I say that?

41
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,520
I'm talking about my son here.

42
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,439
Why are you interrupting blindly?

43
00:02:58,979 --> 00:03:00,120
Please continue.

44
00:03:00,199 --> 00:03:01,460
If I interrupt again,

45
00:03:01,659 --> 00:03:02,699
then he's your son.

46
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:05,860
Divorcing at the drop of a hat.

47
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,060
Isn't that just like the old days,

48
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,960
when men cast off wives at a whim?

49
00:03:10,099 --> 00:03:11,620
That's called being irresponsible.

50
00:03:11,819 --> 00:03:13,520
Once you marry a wife,

51
00:03:13,699 --> 00:03:15,219
training her is up to you.

52
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,819
If she disobeys, you can...

53
00:03:18,139 --> 00:03:19,060
discipline her.

54
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:20,139
You...

55
00:03:20,139 --> 00:03:21,400
That counts as domestic violence.

56
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,520
What do you think?

57
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:25,280
That dead husband of mine back then,

58
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,319
sure didn't spare the violence.

59
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,379
Oh boy.

60
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,719
One wrong word,

61
00:03:28,979 --> 00:03:30,180
and he'd come right at my face.

62
00:03:31,139 --> 00:03:32,240
Where there is oppression,

63
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:33,599
there is resistance.

64
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:35,180
He came at my face,

65
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:36,599
and I kicked and punched.

66
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,780
I'd get desperate and scratch.

67
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,199
I'd scratch his face to shreds.

68
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,000
Luckily,

69
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,639
he croaked.

70
00:03:45,979 --> 00:03:46,759
Croaked.

71
00:03:47,479 --> 00:03:48,039
Passed away.

72
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:49,560
You mean,

73
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:50,780
you...

74
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,039
scratched him to death?

75
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,139
Oh my.

76
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:57,020
With his big build and violent temper,

77
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,620
every time,

78
00:03:59,199 --> 00:04:01,819
he beat me black and blue.

79
00:04:01,819 --> 00:04:02,659
Black eyes.

80
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:06,080
You tell me,

81
00:04:06,539 --> 00:04:07,879
that unlucky son of mine,

82
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:10,319
if he had half his dad's temper,

83
00:04:10,319 --> 00:04:12,740
wouldn't be such a wimp.

84
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:15,460
Domestic violence.

85
00:04:17,579 --> 00:04:20,180
Look at that, why bother?

86
00:04:20,259 --> 00:04:22,259
Hit a thousand times, hurt your hand eight hundred.

87
00:04:22,279 --> 00:04:23,480
It's not worth it.

88
00:04:23,579 --> 00:04:24,139
I...

89
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,839
I'll slap my own mouth.

90
00:04:28,079 --> 00:04:28,980
Yes, master.

91
00:04:32,019 --> 00:04:33,180
Slap your mouth

92
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,720
Who told you to speak?

93
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:38,839
It hurts

94
00:04:38,839 --> 00:04:39,279
I can't take it

95
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,199
Enough

96
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:43,360
I'll ask you one more time

97
00:04:43,939 --> 00:04:45,819
These properties in your mother's hands

98
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,040
where did they come from?

99
00:04:47,139 --> 00:04:48,740
My grandma passed them to her

100
00:04:48,819 --> 00:04:50,180
Why pass them to her?

101
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,459
She is our family's daughter-in-law

102
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:54,920
Am I not?

103
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:56,959
My mom also gave the Chen family

104
00:04:56,959 --> 00:04:57,959
me, this

105
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,980
the only male heir in three generations

106
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,139
Me

107
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,879
I also gave your Chen family

108
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:05,660
the only son for four generations

109
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,220
Right, your contribution is greater

110
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:10,779
Anyway

111
00:05:10,939 --> 00:05:12,819
Since your grandpa's wife

112
00:05:12,899 --> 00:05:15,879
could pass this house to your dad's wife

113
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,399
then your dad's wife

114
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:18,920
should also pass this house

115
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,420
to your wife

116
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:21,860
Makes sense, right?

117
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:22,819
No

118
00:05:22,879 --> 00:05:24,000
No problem

119
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,459
It does make sense

120
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:26,920
But

121
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:27,959
But what?

122
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:29,579
The light changed, let's go

123
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,100
Is that your daughter?

124
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:40,759
Don't talk nonsense

125
00:05:41,759 --> 00:05:42,699
Look who this is

126
00:05:45,699 --> 00:05:46,480
Can't tell, can you?

127
00:05:47,779 --> 00:05:49,220
This is our Ms. Liu

128
00:05:49,819 --> 00:05:51,180
when she was young

129
00:05:51,939 --> 00:05:52,639
Let me see

130
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,199
Let me have a look

131
00:05:54,339 --> 00:05:55,100
Please

132
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:56,060
Just let me see

133
00:05:58,339 --> 00:05:59,199
You don't say

134
00:05:59,199 --> 00:06:01,000
The eyes and brows really do look alike

135
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:02,579
Where did you get this?

136
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:05,800
Cut out from an old magazine

137
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:07,740
What magazine nowadays

138
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,259
would publish such old stills?

139
00:06:09,420 --> 00:06:10,379
Magazines these days

140
00:06:10,779 --> 00:06:11,759
What's strange about that?

141
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:13,399
Is it rare?

142
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,459
This is a magazine from 1965

143
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,480
Young Pioneer

144
00:06:18,439 --> 00:06:19,560
Which issue?

145
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,360
The September issue

146
00:06:21,759 --> 00:06:22,620
How old were you then?

147
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,980
I was already nine

148
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,199
Excuse me

149
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:28,779
When you were only nine

150
00:06:29,839 --> 00:06:32,220
I was already ten years old

151
00:06:45,620 --> 00:06:46,500
Tell me,

152
00:06:46,759 --> 00:06:49,000
if your mom doesn't want the apartment,

153
00:06:49,259 --> 00:06:50,980
and just wants the demolition compensation,

154
00:06:51,279 --> 00:06:54,600
then takes that huge sum of money

155
00:06:54,779 --> 00:06:56,120
and marries some little old man,

156
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:59,040
wouldn't I end up like...

157
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,699
a dog biting a pig's bladder,

158
00:07:00,819 --> 00:07:02,480
happy for nothing?

159
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:04,620
Why would you bite that thing?

160
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,899
That's so gross.

161
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:06,839
If I bite it...

162
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:09,220
that makes me the dog!

163
00:07:09,339 --> 00:07:10,860
Seriously.

164
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,720
It's a metaphor, get it?

165
00:07:13,379 --> 00:07:15,000
Use a better metaphor then.

166
00:07:15,379 --> 00:07:16,879
Like "drawing water with a bamboo basket,"

167
00:07:16,879 --> 00:07:18,399
or "a monkey fishing for the moon."

168
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,699
Then I'll be the monkey fishing.

169
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:23,040
A monkey isn't much better than a dog.

170
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,399
Can't you wish me well?

171
00:07:24,759 --> 00:07:26,959
How could I? How would I dare?

172
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:28,040
Alright.

173
00:07:28,579 --> 00:07:30,100
When we go in later,

174
00:07:30,379 --> 00:07:32,240
let's play the emotional card first.

175
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,160
Whatever the old lady likes to hear,

176
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,259
that's what we'll say.

177
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,339
To soften her stubborn heart.

178
00:07:38,819 --> 00:07:40,939
So what does my mom like to hear?

179
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:42,819
She likes to hear...

180
00:07:43,139 --> 00:07:44,000
How should I know?

181
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,180
She's your mom, not mine.

182
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:45,839
Why ask me?

183
00:07:46,019 --> 00:07:47,399
You two don't get along anyway.

184
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:49,480
My mom probably won't like anything you say.

185
00:07:50,860 --> 00:07:51,839
Fine.

186
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:53,779
How about this?

187
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,379
When we go in,

188
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,680
I won't say a word.

189
00:07:56,779 --> 00:07:58,120
You do all the talking, okay?

190
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,800
That works. My mom...

191
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:01,800
seeing how you usually

192
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,560
boss me around, she can't stand it.

193
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:04,740
If I could...

194
00:08:04,819 --> 00:08:06,019
you know, lecture you,

195
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:07,060
scold you,

196
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,079
tell you off...

197
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,500
my mom would definitely be happy to see that.

198
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,660
Don't get me wrong.

199
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,560
Fine.

200
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,620
However you tell me off in there,

201
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:18,779
I'll take it.

202
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:20,420
I'll be totally submissive.

203
00:08:20,620 --> 00:08:21,519
I won't make a peep.

204
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,319
Will that work?

205
00:08:22,379 --> 00:08:24,779
Really? Then it'd be best if I...

206
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,040
start cursing immediately,

207
00:08:26,079 --> 00:08:27,139
and raise my hand to hit you.

208
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:28,800
My mom would be even happier to see that.

209
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:30,199
Okay.

210
00:08:30,879 --> 00:08:32,820
What do you mean "okay"?

211
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:33,360
Wait a minute.

212
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,940
You actually want to hit me?

213
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,759
You damn Dabao!

214
00:08:35,879 --> 00:08:37,039
I wouldn't dare! Just kidding.

215
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,340
How could I bear to hit you?

216
00:08:38,419 --> 00:08:41,080
That son of mine is so spineless.

217
00:08:41,179 --> 00:08:43,179
Every time he goes shopping with his wife,

218
00:08:44,779 --> 00:08:45,460
he trots along eagerly,

219
00:08:45,460 --> 00:08:46,600
trotting right behind her,

220
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:48,840
carrying bags in both hands.

221
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,759
He probably has one in his mouth too.

222
00:08:51,639 --> 00:08:54,000
But that daughter-in-law, that little fox,

223
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,299
is completely empty-handed.

224
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:56,200
She's out in front,

225
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:56,700
just...

226
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:57,860
sashaying,

227
00:08:57,860 --> 00:08:58,440
sashaying along.

228
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,200
Mom.

229
00:09:03,259 --> 00:09:04,600
Am I seeing things?

230
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:05,899
Mom.

231
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:08,659
Am I hearing things?

232
00:09:08,919 --> 00:09:09,639
What's wrong, Mom?

233
00:09:10,179 --> 00:09:12,340
She just called me "Mom."

234
00:09:12,419 --> 00:09:13,600
Was she calling me?

235
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,820
Obviously.

236
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:16,120
If she doesn't call you Mom,

237
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,820
what else would she call you?

238
00:09:19,419 --> 00:09:20,759
Usually she calls me...

239
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,019
Or just "Old Lady."

240
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:24,419
She wouldn't dare.

241
00:09:25,179 --> 00:09:25,960
Hu Xiaoli!

242
00:09:26,379 --> 00:09:27,559
Why are you just standing there?

243
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,820
Hurry up and take the stuff...

244
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,440
...into my mom's room.

245
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:34,200
Okay!

246
00:09:35,340 --> 00:09:36,700
Show some awareness.

247
00:09:36,980 --> 00:09:39,039
See if there are any seasonal clothes in the room...

248
00:09:39,039 --> 00:09:40,559
...and wash them all for me.

249
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:41,620
Okay!

250
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:44,399
Is there something wrong with my brain?

251
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,759
Why are you pinching me?

252
00:09:47,779 --> 00:09:49,519
I'm checking if I'm dreaming.

253
00:09:49,759 --> 00:09:51,320
No, then you should pinch yourself.

254
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:51,899
Or you can pinch...

255
00:09:51,899 --> 00:09:52,480
...pinch him.

256
00:09:54,759 --> 00:09:55,460
Dabao.

257
00:09:55,659 --> 00:09:56,139
Mom.

258
00:09:56,139 --> 00:09:57,580
Did something happen to our family?

259
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:58,139
No.

260
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:58,919
Nothing happened.

261
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,139
Impossible.

262
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,820
Otherwise, why are you acting like this?

263
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:03,879
And why is she acting like that?

264
00:10:04,559 --> 00:10:05,539
You mean...

265
00:10:05,659 --> 00:10:07,580
...how she usually gives you attitude?

266
00:10:07,659 --> 00:10:09,440
And is fierce towards me, right?

267
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:10,299
Mom.

268
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,100
That's all just on the surface.

269
00:10:12,159 --> 00:10:13,700
It's an illusion.

270
00:10:14,340 --> 00:10:15,639
It's because she...

271
00:10:16,019 --> 00:10:17,440
...is afraid of me.

272
00:10:17,620 --> 00:10:18,539
Because she...

273
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,919
...respects you.

274
00:10:22,139 --> 00:10:24,440
Usually she pulls a long face,

275
00:10:24,539 --> 00:10:25,940
speaks nastily,

276
00:10:26,139 --> 00:10:27,620
and makes indirect accusations.

277
00:10:27,899 --> 00:10:29,960
So that turns out to be respect for me?

278
00:10:30,059 --> 00:10:30,940
Exactly.

279
00:10:31,039 --> 00:10:33,379
She's learning from you.

280
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,419
Back in the day, you...

281
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,759
...didn't you treat my dad exactly like that?

282
00:10:35,759 --> 00:10:37,000
You're talking nonsense!

283
00:10:37,559 --> 00:10:38,259
Back then...

284
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:40,480
...if I dared to push my luck like she does,

285
00:10:40,639 --> 00:10:42,399
your dad wouldn't even need to lift a finger.

286
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,960
His grandma would have slapped me long ago.

287
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:46,299
Mom.

288
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:47,659
We have to give her...

289
00:10:47,799 --> 00:10:49,700
...a chance to repent.

290
00:10:49,919 --> 00:10:51,120
After all, this Hu Xiaoli...

291
00:10:51,259 --> 00:10:52,340
...for our Chen family...

292
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,000
...gave birth to a big grandson.

293
00:10:54,059 --> 00:10:56,100
